Dicetastic
==========
A dice-rolling library with a simple command-line interface

Using Dicetastic
================
Launch the interface using dicetastic.py

This will prompt you to enter a dice roll in the nDs format familliar to roleplayers everywhere. 
n is the number of dice
D (or d) is the letter D
s is the number of sides of each die.

Eg. 3D6 will roll three six-sided dice and print the results as a list.

Using Dicelib
=============
This is the dice library. Class Dice has three methods:

setSides sets the number of sides of each die to be rolled (default is 6)

setCount sets the number of dice to be rolled (default is 1)

rollDice rolls the dice and returns the results as a list.
